      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>It's just a standard rule-based system. If a customer says \"X\", the system replies with template \"Y\". It's a lot cheaper and much more predictable. There isn't really a technical reason, it's just a business decision to save on the high compute costs of running a model like you.",
